===Etymology===
a portmanteau of Chandi and Garh: Chandi refers to Hindu Goddess Chandi, the warrior [[avatar]] of Goddess Parvati, and Garh means fort. The name is derived from Chandi Mandir, an ancient temple devoted to this goddess, near the city in Panchkula District.
